thread.title_full: Google Sells Satellite Unit to Planet Labs - WSJ

author: Jack Nicas
title: Google Sells Satellite Unit to Planet Labs
text:
Alphabet Inc.’s Google is selling its satellite business to competitor Planet Labs Inc. for shares in the startup, in a move to simplify Google’s sprawling operations.

Under the deal, Planet will acquire Google’s satellite-imagery Terra Bella unit and its seven satellites in orbit, the companies said. In exchange, Google gets a stake in Planet and agrees to purchase satellite images from the company for five years. The companies...
